{"timestamp": 1772712833.753578, "task_id": "gen-20260305180810-2022", "task_type": "code", "description": "Implement retry logic with error handling", "result": {"success": true, "agent": "coder", "duration": 11.150840044021606, "output": "I'll need a bit more context to give you the most useful implementation. A few quick questions:\n\n- What language/framework are you working in?\n- Is this for HTTP requests, database calls, or something else?\n- Do you have existing code you want to add retry logic to?\n\nThat said, here's a solid general-purpose retry utility in TypeScript that covers the common cases:\n\n```typescript\ninterface RetryOptions {\n  maxAttempts?: number;\n  delayMs?: number;\n  backoff?: \"fixed\" | \"exponential\";\n  retryIf?: (error: unknown) => boolean;\n  onRetry?: (error: unknown, attempt: number) => void;\n}\n\nasync function withRetry<T>(\n  fn: () => Promise<T>,\n  options: RetryOptions = {}\n): Promise<T> {\n  const {\n    maxAttempts = 3,\n    delayMs = 500,\n    backoff = \"exponential\",\n    retryIf = () => true,\n    onRetry,\n  } = options;\n\n  let lastError: unknown;\n\n  for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= maxAttempts; attempt++) {\n    try {\n      return await fn();\n    } catch (error) {\n      lastError = error;\n\n      const isLastAttempt = attempt === maxAttempts;\n      if (isLastAttempt || !retryIf(error)) {\n        throw error;\n      }\n\n      onRetry?.(error, attempt);\n\n      const delay =\n        backoff === \"exponential\"\n          ? delayMs * Math.pow(2, attempt - 1)\n          : delayMs;\n\n      await sleep(delay);\n    }\n  }\n\n  throw lastError;\n}\n\nconst sleep = (ms: number) => new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n```\n\nUsage examples:\n\n```typescript\n// Basic usage\nconst data = await withRetry(() => fetchSomeData());\n\n// HTTP request with selective retry (skip 4xx errors)\nconst result = await withRetry(() => fetch(\"/api/resource\"), {\n  maxAttempts: 4,\n  delayMs: 300,\n  backoff: \"exponential\",\n  retryIf: (err) => !(err instanceof HttpError && err.status < 500),\n  onRetry: (err, attempt) => console.warn(`Attempt ${attempt} failed:`, err),\n});\n\n// Fixed delay, fewer retries\nconst record = await withRetry(() => db.query(\"SELECT ...\"), {\n  maxAttempts: 2,\n  delayMs: 1000,\n  backoff: \"fixed\",\n});\n```\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Exponential backoff by default (500ms → 1s → 2s)\n- `retryIf` lets you skip retries for non-recoverable errors (like 400/401/403)\n- `onRetry` hook for logging or metrics\n- Always re-throws the original error after exhausting attempts\n\nIf you share your specific use case or existing code, I can tailor this to fit right in.", "tokens": {"input": 2861, "output": 706}}, "retry_count": 0, "total_attempts": 1}
