on\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm link  # Makes the CLI globally available\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Create a Backup\n\n```bash\n# Backup a directory\nbackup-cli create ./my-project\n\n# Backup with custom name\nbackup-cli create ./my-project -n my-backup-name\n\n# Backup to custom directory\nbackup-cli create ./my-project -d /path/to/backups\n\n# Backup with specific compression level (0-9)\nbackup-cli create ./my-project -c 5\n```\n\n### List Backups\n\n```bash\nbackup-cli list\n\n# List backups from custom directory\nbackup-cli list -d /path/to/backups\n```\n\n### Restore a Backup\n\n```bash\nbackup-cli restore backup-name ./restore-location\n\n# Restore from custom backup directory\nbackup-cli restore backup-name ./restore-location -d /path/to/backups\n```\n\n### Delete a Backup\n\n```bash\nbackup-cli delete backup-name\n\n# Delete from custom backup directory\nbackup-cli delete backup-name -d /path/to/backups\n```\n\n## Options\n\n- `-n, --name <name>` - Custom backup name\n- `-d, --dir <dir>` - Backup directory (default: ./backups)\n- `-c, --compression <level>` - Compression level 0-9 (default: 9)\n\n## Examples\n\n```bash\n# Create a backup of your project\nbackup-cli create ./my-app -n project-backup-v1\n\n# List all backups\nbackup-cli list\n\n# Restore a specific backup\nbackup-cli restore project-backup-v1 ./restored-app\n\n# Delete an old backup\nbackup-cli delete old-backup-name\n```\n\n## Backup Manifest\n\nThe tool maintains a `manifest.json` file in the backup directory that tracks:\n- Backup name and timestamp\n- Source path\n- File size\n- Backup type (full/incremental)\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n</content>\n</write_to_file>\n\nCreated a full-featured CLI backup tool with:\n\n- **Backup creation** with compression (ZIP format)\n- **Restore functionality** to extract backups\n- **List command** showing all backups with metadata\n- **Delete command** to remove old backups\n- **Manifest tracking** for backup history\n- **Customizable options** for compression