{"timestamp": 1772713313.285724, "task_id": "gen-20260305180810-5489", "task_type": "code", "description": "Implement logging with error handling", "result": {"success": true, "agent": "coder", "duration": 8.85585618019104, "output": "I'll implement a logging utility with error handling.\n\n```python\n# logger.py\nimport logging\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n\ndef setup_logger(\n    name: str,\n    log_file: Optional[str] = None,\n    level: int = logging.INFO,\n) -> logging.Logger:\n    \"\"\"Configure and return a logger with console and optional file handlers.\"\"\"\n    logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n    logger.setLevel(level)\n\n    formatter = logging.Formatter(\n        fmt=\"%(asctime)s | %(levelname)-8s | %(name)s | %(message)s\",\n        datefmt=\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\",\n    )\n\n    # Console handler\n    console_handler = logging.StreamHandler(sys.stdout)\n    console_handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n    logger.addHandler(console_handler)\n\n    # File handler (optional)\n    if log_file:\n        try:\n            Path(log_file).parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n            file_handler = logging.FileHandler(log_file, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n            file_handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n            logger.addHandler(file_handler)\n        except OSError as e:\n            logger.error(\"Failed to create log file '%s': %s\", log_file, e)\n\n    return logger\n\n\ndef log_error(logger: logging.Logger, message: str, exc: Optional[Exception] = None) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Log an error with optional exception traceback.\"\"\"\n    if exc:\n        logger.error(\"%s: %s\", message, exc, exc_info=True)\n    else:\n        logger.error(message)\n\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    log = setup_logger(\"app\", log_file=\"logs/app.log\", level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n    log.info(\"Application started\")\n    log.debug(\"Debug details here\")\n\n    try:\n        result = 1 / 0\n    except ZeroDivisionError as e:\n        log_error(log, \"Calculation failed\", exc=e)\n\n    log.warning(\"Low memory warning\")\n    log.info(\"Application finished\")\n```\n\nKey points:\n- `setup_logger` handles both console and file output, creating parent dirs automatically\n- File handler failures are caught and reported without crashing the app\n- `log_error` attaches full tracebacks when an exception is passed\n- Formatter includes timestamp, level, and logger name for easy filtering\n\nRun it with `python logger.py` and you'll see output in the console and `logs/app.log`.", "tokens": {"input": 3113, "output": 666}}, "retry_count": 0, "total_attempts": 1}
