{"timestamp": 1772744741.6329072, "task_id": "gen-20260305180810-4573", "task_type": "tool", "description": "Convert CSV to Markdown", "result": {"success": true, "agent": "coder", "duration": 8.590760946273804, "output": "Here's a simple CSV to Markdown table converter:\n\n```python\nimport csv\nimport sys\nfrom io import StringIO\n\ndef csv_to_markdown(csv_content: str) -> str:\n    reader = csv.reader(StringIO(csv_content.strip()))\n    rows = list(reader)\n    \n    if not rows:\n        return \"\"\n    \n    headers = rows[0]\n    col_widths = [len(h) for h in headers]\n    \n    for row in rows[1:]:\n        for i, cell in enumerate(row):\n            if i < len(col_widths):\n                col_widths[i] = max(col_widths[i], len(cell))\n    \n    def fmt_row(row):\n        return \"| \" + \" | \".join(cell.ljust(col_widths[i]) for i, cell in enumerate(row)) + \" |\"\n    \n    separator = \"| \" + \" | \".join(\"-\" * w for w in col_widths) + \" |\"\n    \n    lines = [fmt_row(headers), separator]\n    lines += [fmt_row(row) for row in rows[1:]]\n    \n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) > 1:\n        with open(sys.argv[1], \"r\") as f:\n            print(csv_to_markdown(f.read()))\n    else:\n        print(csv_to_markdown(sys.stdin.read()))\n```\n\nUsage:\n\n```bash\n# from a file\npython csv_to_md.py data.csv\n\n# from stdin\necho \"name,age,city\nAlice,30,NYC\nBob,25,LA\" | python csv_to_md.py\n```\n\nOutput for that example:\n\n```\n| name  | age | city |\n| ----- | --- | ---- |\n| Alice | 30  | NYC  |\n| Bob   | 25  | LA   |\n```\n\nIf you want a one-liner for quick use, `pandas` also handles this cleanly:\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\nprint(pd.read_csv(\"data.csv\").to_markdown(index=False))\n```\n\n(requires `pip install pandas tabulate`)", "tokens": {"input": 3302, "output": 456}}, "retry_count": 0, "total_attempts": 1}
